history.content: I believe that it's normal for it to show up as soon as you submit the part 1 form; I'm finishing my last class for the minor this semester but it's been on my CalCentral ever since I submitted the paperwork. You get some special privileges for having the CS minor, like a 199 instructional account that you can use for getting into Soda after hours/printing even if you aren't taking any CS classes that semester.
You're now declared in the minor, just like your major. Everything is as it should be.

For the CS minor, I completed 4 of the prereqs and submitted part 1 of the minor form. I got an email today and the minor now shows on Cal Central. Is this an error? I didn't know the minor was going to show up until I've taken all 7 classes...
